body:
This works:
```cython
cdef extern from *: 
    """ 
    template<typename T> 
    T sum(T a, T b) { 
        return a + b; 
    } 
    template<typename T> 
    T sum(T a, T b, T c) { 
        return a + b + c; 
    } 
    """ 
    T sum[T](T a, T b) 
    T sum[T](T a, T b, T c) 
 
print(sum[int](1, 2)) 
print(sum[int](1, 2, 3)) 
```

This doesn't:
```cython
cdef extern from *: 
    """ 
    template<typename T1, typename T2> 
    T1 sum(T1 a, T2 b) { 
        return a + b; 
    } 
    template<typename T1, typename T2, typename T3> 
    T1 sum(T1 a, T2 b, T3 c) { 
        return a + b + c; 
    } 
    """ 
    T1 sum[T1, T2](T1 a, T2 b) 
    T1 sum[T1, T2, T3](T1 a, T2 b, T3 c) 
 
print(sum[int, int](1, 2)) 
print(sum[int, int, int](1, 2, 3)) 
```

```
Error compiling Cython file:
------------------------------------------------------------
...
    }
    """
    T1 sum[T1, T2](T1 a, T2 b)
    T1 sum[T1, T2, T3](T1 a, T2 b, T3 c)

print(sum[int, int](1, 2))
        ^
------------------------------------------------------------

test.pyx:15:9: Wrong number of template arguments: expected 3, got 2
```
title: Overloading template functions with different numbers of template parameters
